{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-post-js","path":"/writing/personal-website-refresh-2020/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>In this post, I will tell you some of the things behind the personal website refresh. But most of the reason is about <a href=\"https://afnizarnur.com/writing/giving-back-to-community/\">giving back to community</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"design-tools-i-use\"><a href=\"#design-tools-i-use\" aria-label=\"design tools i use permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Design tools I use</h3>\n<p>Designer, I know you love tools, and we know you also love the design process. I will share my design process for building portfolio in another post, so don’t worry.</p>\n<p>In this project, I use the power combo of <a href=\"https://sketch.com/\">Sketch</a> and <a href=\"abstract.com/\">Abstract</a> (Designer’s version control–it’s like GitHub).</p>\n<p>Before I started this project, I really never use Abstract in my workflow. Luckily my company I work on is in progress adopting Abstract, so as part of learning the mindset of version control for designer, I use Abstract for my portfolio. I’m thinking of moving this project to Figma at another time.</p>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"margin: 0\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1332c05cdee051d0c18349ec366e9031/ac99c/abstract-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1536px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 63.541666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"My Portfolio Project on Abstract\"\n        title=\"My Portfolio Project on Abstract\"\n        src=\"/static/1332c05cdee051d0c18349ec366e9031/ac99c/abstract-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1332c05cdee051d0c18349ec366e9031/4ecad/abstract-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg 384w,\n/static/1332c05cdee051d0c18349ec366e9031/212bf/abstract-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg 768w,\n/static/1332c05cdee051d0c18349ec366e9031/ac99c/abstract-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg 1536w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">My Portfolio Project on Abstract</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      \n\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"margin: 0\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3afdc2198467868415accf8f206ce8ce/ac99c/sketch-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1536px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 63.541666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"My Portfolio Project on Sketch\"\n        title=\"My Sketch File\"\n        src=\"/static/3afdc2198467868415accf8f206ce8ce/ac99c/sketch-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3afdc2198467868415accf8f206ce8ce/4ecad/sketch-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg 384w,\n/static/3afdc2198467868415accf8f206ce8ce/212bf/sketch-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg 768w,\n/static/3afdc2198467868415accf8f206ce8ce/ac99c/sketch-afnizarnur-portfolio.jpg 1536w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">My Sketch File</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </p>\n<h3 id=\"the-technology-stack\"><a href=\"#the-technology-stack\" aria-label=\"the technology stack permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The technology stack</h3>\n<p>I always want to be a front-end engineer because I’m curious about anything about web technology. This site using <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/\">Gatsby.js</a> as the framework, a React-based static site generator. Currently using JavaScript, maybe I’ll move it to TypeScript as part of learning!</p>\n<p>I already learning Gatsby.js maybe a year as a hobbyist. Not just following the hype but to learn more about how React works in a framework and the magic of the system behind it.</p>\n<p>Proudly deploying this site in Netlify. I have been their user since 2017; I really love the support team and the community forum because they’re beneficial for helping me when I got a problem when deploying projects.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>I think that’s it! This is a super short blog post, I know. I just want to be more frequently to write anything. If you’re reading it until the end of the page, let’s connect on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/afnizarnur\">Twitter</a>.</p>","id":"ad58c85b-b271-55d4-ae15-f00872708376","frontmatter":{"title":"Personal Website Refresh","date":"April 10, 2020","datetime":"April 10th, 2020","description":"It's time to launch my personal website, again and it's always a work in progress.","category":"Personal","tags":["thoughts","portfolio","website","development","react"]},"fields":{"slug":"/writing/personal-website-refresh-2020/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/writing/personal-website-refresh-2020/"}}}